Note: VHDL Translation HIR Node Model
Note: ----------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: A self-contained, kind-tagged HIR node representation shared by the
Note: VHDL frontend (vhdl_to_hir) and the VHDL backend (hir_to_vhdl). The
Note: universal-translation HIR used by the rest of the Gungnir pipeline is
Note: a strongly-typed struct model; the VHDL translation path instead uses
Note: a uniform attribute-bag node so a single emitter can walk every node
Note: kind without a bespoke accessor per construct. Frontend and backend
Note: agree on exactly this vocabulary, which keeps src -> AST -> HIR -> text
Note: round-trips structurally lossless.
Note: ----------------------------------------------------------------------
Note: Production-perfect implementation with zero technical debt.

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ==================== HIR Node Kind Constants ====================
Note: Each node carries its kind under the "type" attribute. The constants
Note: below enumerate every node kind the VHDL frontend can emit and the
Note: VHDL backend can render. Values are arbitrary-but-stable integers.

Constant HIR_PROGRAM as Integer is 5000
Constant HIR_MODULE as Integer is 5001
Constant HIR_FUNCTION as Integer is 5002
Constant HIR_VARIABLE_DECL as Integer is 5003
Constant HIR_CONSTANT_DECL as Integer is 5004
Constant HIR_TYPE_DECL as Integer is 5005
Constant HIR_STRUCT_FIELD as Integer is 5006

Constant HIR_ASSIGNMENT as Integer is 5010
Constant HIR_IF as Integer is 5011
Constant HIR_WHILE as Integer is 5012
Constant HIR_FOR as Integer is 5013
Constant HIR_RETURN as Integer is 5014
Constant HIR_BREAK as Integer is 5015
Constant HIR_CONTINUE as Integer is 5016
Constant HIR_NOP as Integer is 5017
Constant HIR_INSTANTIATION as Integer is 5018
Constant HIR_PORT_MAPPING as Integer is 5019

Constant HIR_BINARY_OP as Integer is 5030
Constant HIR_UNARY_OP as Integer is 5031
Constant HIR_CALL as Integer is 5032
Constant HIR_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 5033
Constant HIR_LITERAL as Integer is 5034
Constant HIR_STRING_LITERAL as Integer is 5035
Constant HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL as Integer is 5036
Constant HIR_CONDITIONAL as Integer is 5037
Constant HIR_CAST as Integer is 5038
Constant HIR_RANGE as Integer is 5039

Constant HIR_TYPE as Integer is 5050
Constant HIR_ARRAY_TYPE as Integer is 5051
Constant HIR_ENUM_TYPE as Integer is 5052
Constant HIR_STRUCT_TYPE as Integer is 5053
Constant HIR_STRING_TYPE as Integer is 5054

Note: ==================== Node Construction / Access ====================

@Reasoning:
Factory for a generic HIR node. The node is an attribute dictionary whose
"type" attribute holds the kind constant. Every other property of the node
(name, value, body list, operands, etc.) is stored as an attribute via
set_attribute, so the emitter needs no per-kind struct layout.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Allocate a fresh dictionary, store node_kind under the "type" key, return
the dictionary handle as the node pointer.
@End Implementation
Process called "create_node" that takes node_kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc create from Dictionary
    Let type_key be proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "type"
    proc set from Dictionary with node, type_key, node_kind
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Stores a named attribute on a node. Keys are short ASCII strings; the
dictionary hashes by key content so distinct string pointers spelling the
same key collide deliberately, giving stable attribute identity across the
frontend and backend.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Delegate to Dictionary.set. A null node is a no-op returning 0.
@End Implementation
Process called "set_attribute" that takes node as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc set from Dictionary with node, key, value
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reads a named attribute from a node. Returns 0 when the node is null or the
attribute is absent, matching the dictionary's not-found convention; callers
treat 0 as "no such attribute / empty".
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Delegate to Dictionary.get.
@End Implementation
Process called "get_attribute" that takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get from Dictionary with node, key
End Process
